The Adamawa state government is set to reintroduce taxi transport services to improve the security of commuters and Internally Generated Revenue (IGR) of the state. Mustapha Jika, Commissioner Ministry for Transportation, told newsmen in Yola, Wednesday, that the program is part of new reform towards safeguarding lives and properties of commuters. Jika assured that, identity of the cab drivers could easily be established traced  by the ministry, against tricycle riders who are mostly non indigenes from other states. “People resort to using tricycle popularly known as ‘Keke-NAPEP’ because there was no alternatives, hence the need for intra state cabs. “Boarding tricycle around 9:00 pm within the state, could expose people to insecurity,” he maintained. The Commissioner debunk fare list being circulated on social media reiterating that state transport company  is fully in compliance with the inter-state lockdown order. The state would soon procure boats to reduce over dependence on road transportation between Nigeria and Cameroon through the River Benue. 